Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.66,0:01:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My father died suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.66,0:01:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I only found out last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.16,0:01:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor called to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.67,0:01:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I couldn't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.67,0:01:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My hometown is in the mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.17,0:01:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}a village called Sanhetun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.17,0:01:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I left to work in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.68,0:01:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'm so busy I haven't been home in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.18,0:01:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My father was the village schoolteacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.68,0:01:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He taught there all his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.19,0:01:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I am an only child.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.69,0:01:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The only one from our village who went to college.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.19,0:01:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I am very worried about my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.23,0:02:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Come in and rest a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.24,0:02:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I've got to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.24,0:02:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Thank your boss again for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.24,0:02:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- Thank you.    - Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.26,0:02:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.76,0:02:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yusheng.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.27,0:02:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mayor, Uncle Xia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.77,0:02:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I saw the car and knew you were back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.77,0:02:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:02:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's warmer inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Please. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I couldn't tell you much over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.29,0:03:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Now you're here, I can explain everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's the schoolhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}For many years your father has wanted to rebuild it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but there were always reasons we couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He brought it up again recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.80,0:03:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and the village agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We have the materials we need but not enough money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your father's mind was set.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He was determined to find the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He began traveling around, trying to borrow the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He went all over the county.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.83,0:03:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}If he thought there was a chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.83,0:03:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}he'd go after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.33,0:03:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}On the last trip, on his way home...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}he ran into a snowstorm, a big blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He was stuck in the storm, and he got sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.83,0:03:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He was too sick to be moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.84,0:03:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That made him more anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He was in bad shape when he got back,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.34,0:04:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}so we took him to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.84,0:04:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They examined him, said he had a heart problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.85,0:04:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We've known your dad all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.85,0:04:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Who knew he had a heart condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.85,0:04:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They tried treating him, but it was no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He fought, but he didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Where is my father now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.36,0:04:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}At the provincial hospital, in the morgue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's why we wanted you to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.87,0:04:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}To tell you all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.37,0:04:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Last time I spoke with him, he seemed fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It was a bad storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}At his age, it was too much for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.38,0:04:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.88,0:04:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}hard on anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.39,0:04:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The village wants to arrange a car
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}to bring your father back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.89,0:04:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- It's been three days.    - Bring him back here to bury him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.90,0:05:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's what we planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's fine. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}But there is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.91,0:05:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your mother doesn't want to use a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.41,0:05:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She wants your father to be carried back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She wants the coffin brought back on foot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}so your father won't forget his way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.93,0:05:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- It's an old tradition, a superstition.    - I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}And she wants to walk with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.93,0:05:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}So let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He was our village teacher. Everyone respects him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.44,0:05:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}But our young people have all left for the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They've gone away to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.95,0:05:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Only old people and children are left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.95,0:05:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We thought of using a tractor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We could make the trip in half a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.96,0:05:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You must help your mother decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:06:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I appreciate your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I will talk it over with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.24,0:06:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- Good.    - Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:11.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Probably at the schoolhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She's there every day since he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.48,0:06:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- She won't listen to anyone.    - She just sits there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- Is she okay?    - I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.48,0:06:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I am only afraid--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.48,0:06:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The old schoolhouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.49,0:06:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'll go to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.51,0:06:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- Mother.    - Yusheng.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.02,0:06:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's so cold. Let's go home, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.52,0:07:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your father is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.03,0:07:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You will never see him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.06,0:07:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Get on the bed where it's warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.10,0:07:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yusheng. Bring me my loom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.08,0:07:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I want to weave something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.58,0:07:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Weave what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}A cloth for your father's coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Don't trouble yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why don't we go buy one instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.59,0:08:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't want to buy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.59,0:08:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That loom is so old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.10,0:08:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's been broken for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why can't we fix it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You need rest, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.30,0:08:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You must be so tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.61,0:08:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I have to make this cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.12,0:08:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Can't I just buy one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.12,0:08:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No, just bring me the loom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.15,0:09:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The only loom left in the village...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}his this one of your mother's.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.16,0:09:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She's guarded it like a treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.16,0:09:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Looks like she's determined to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.66,0:09:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Just like the funeral procession.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.17,0:09:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Carrying the dead is an old custom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Over the mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.18,0:09:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}across the river, past the crossroads.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}And we shout at him along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What do we say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.68,0:09:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We tell him this is the road home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Everyone yells at him,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}so that he remembers his way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's an old tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is it really so difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}to do as my mother wishes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.20,0:09:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It is a problem, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We don't have the manpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.70,0:10:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}All our young people have left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.71,0:10:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No one has followed this custom...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.71,0:10:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}since the Cultural Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't want her to work like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but I don't know how to stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.73,0:10:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The funeral procession...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.73,0:10:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}seems all that matters to her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother, I know about your wishes for the funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.75,0:10:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:11:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is there some other way to arrange it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.76,0:11:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I know it won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.77,0:11:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}But your father lived here for 40 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.77,0:11:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He taught many generations of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.78,0:11:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He worked very hard. Long, long hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.28,0:11:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The town should give him something back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor agrees with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We can walk alongside...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.79,0:11:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}with the coffin pulled by a tractor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.30,0:11:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We'd still be with him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.80,0:11:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's not the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.80,0:11:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I want your father carried back...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.31,0:11:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}by the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.31,0:11:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}If they won't help...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.82,0:11:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}we'll get someone who will.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Please don't work anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I have to. I have to finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.33,0:12:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You are tired. Get some rest, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You sleep in your father's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.34,0:12:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I have to finish this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.40,0:13:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This picture was taken the year my parents married.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My father was not from the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.41,0:13:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He came here to teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.42,0:13:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The story of my parents' courtship...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}is well-known in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Practically everyone here has heard about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother had just turned 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.93,0:13:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My father was 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother told me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.93,0:13:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my father arrived by horse cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.45,0:14:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.95,0:14:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.98,0:14:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This is our new teacher, Mr. Luo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- His name is Luo, Luo Changyu.    - Just call me Luo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is that Di?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.54,0:15:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What's all the racket for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.04,0:15:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.54,0:15:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Has the teacher arrived?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.05,0:15:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.55,0:15:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's about time we got our own teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.55,0:15:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What does he look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He's a young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.56,0:15:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}A young teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He must be talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Where is he staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.56,0:16:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}At the village council office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.57,0:16:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Where will he eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He'll eat with a different family each day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.07,0:16:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When it's our turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.58,0:16:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}we'll have to make a good meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.09,0:16:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Seeing a teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}has you changing clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.60,0:16:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My grandmother was already blind by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother says when Grandfather died...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.36,0:16:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Grandmother cried until she went blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}After Grandfather died,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.11,0:16:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}there was only Mother to look after Grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.62,0:16:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Grandmother's only wish
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:16:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}was to find a good husband for Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.62,0:17:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She had many proposals...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.12,0:17:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but my mother didn't like any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The schoolhouse was not yet built
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}when my father arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor enlisted all the men's help.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.64,0:17:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}According to our village custom...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.14,0:17:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}a red cloth must be hung in a new building.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.64,0:17:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's hung on the ceiling beam for good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.65,0:17:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The cloth is called the lucky red banner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.70,0:17:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It must be woven
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.30,0:17:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}by the village's most beautiful maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This task, of course, fell to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.16,0:17:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Perhaps she was already a little in love...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}because the cloth she made was especially fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.67,0:17:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The village had two wells back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.68,0:17:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The old well was called the "front well."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:17:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The newer well was called the "back well."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The new well was nearer the village,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}so more people used that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.18,0:18:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}After my father arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother started to use the old well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.19,0:18:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She had to pass the schoolhouse to get to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The village had another custom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.25,0:19:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When putting up a new building,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.25,0:19:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}each family prepared a dish for the workers' lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.76,0:19:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Everyone contributed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.76,0:19:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother prepared all her best dishes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}hoping Father would eat what she made.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.79,0:19:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Back then when something was built...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.29,0:19:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}women were not allowed to participate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.29,0:19:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Superstition said they would bring bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.30,0:19:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When they put up the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.30,0:20:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}the village women could only watch
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.83,0:20:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What did you make today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.33,0:20:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Steamed bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.33,0:20:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What about you, Di?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.80,0:20:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I made onion cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.35,0:20:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I brought rice steamed in lotus leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.40,0:20:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Onion cakes are better.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.30,0:20:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Did you save some for your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.84,0:20:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.00,0:20:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Look at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.35,0:20:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They just pick up the first dish they see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.35,0:20:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They don't know who made what.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't know who's eating mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.35,0:20:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Must be your husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.86,0:21:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Put them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.92,0:22:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You're already done with the banner?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.92,0:22:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I was going to come get it from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.90,0:22:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.43,0:22:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.43,0:22:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You'll save me a further trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.93,0:22:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This is a beautiful banner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The school is almost finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.94,0:22:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Chinese study will be the first lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.94,0:22:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is the teacher happy with the food?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.44,0:22:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.95,0:22:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Does he eat what we make?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.45,0:22:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.45,0:22:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He eats together with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.45,0:22:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No. He's a city gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.45,0:22:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's not proper for him to eat with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.45,0:22:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}So how does it work?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.46,0:22:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We give him first pick of the dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.05,0:24:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"In life--" Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.05,0:24:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"In life--"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.56,0:24:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"You must make goals."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.61,0:24:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"You must make goals."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.66,0:24:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Start from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.06,0:24:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"One must learn to write." Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.07,0:24:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"One must learn to write."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.07,0:24:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"One must learn arithmetic."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.58,0:24:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"One must learn arithmetic."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.58,0:24:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Keep a journal faithfully."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.08,0:24:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Keep a journal faithfully."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.59,0:24:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Know the present, know the past."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.59,0:24:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Know the present, know the past."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.10,0:24:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When I was young, my mother told me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.60,0:25:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my father had a beautiful voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.60,0:25:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother never learned to write,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.10,0:25:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}was never interested in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.61,0:25:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}But she couldn't resist the sound of my father's voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.11,0:25:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She went by the school every day after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.11,0:25:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}For most, the novelty of the new school wore off after a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.60,0:25:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but not for my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.62,0:25:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}For 40 years, she came to listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.62,0:25:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and it became part of her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.63,0:25:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Know respect for your elders."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.13,0:25:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Know respect for your elders."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.65,0:25:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Each day after school...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.15,0:25:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my father walked some of his students home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.16,0:26:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Knowing this, my mother waited along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.19,0:26:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}♪ The birds sing with the beautiful sun ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.70,0:26:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}♪ Their songs wake the beautiful flowers ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.65,0:31:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.67,0:31:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Who is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.17,0:31:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's Zhao Di.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.68,0:31:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is she from Sanhetun?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.68,0:31:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.68,0:31:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di, the teacher is asking about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.79,0:33:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You need water?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.29,0:33:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.29,0:33:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Let me get it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.31,0:33:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.30,0:33:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Let me do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.30,0:33:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I can do it. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.80,0:33:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No, let me. Let me help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.80,0:33:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You're the teacher. You shouldn't bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.81,0:34:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Let me do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.31,0:34:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.31,0:34:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.48,0:34:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Let me do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.10,0:34:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di, you're fetching water as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.34,0:34:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Tomorrow it's our turn to have you over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.34,0:34:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.92,0:35:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My father told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.92,0:36:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}the first time he went to my mother's house,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.93,0:36:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}she stood in the doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.93,0:36:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Leaning against the door frame...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.93,0:36:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}she looked like a figure in a painting...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.44,0:36:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}an image he would never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.95,0:36:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is the teacher here?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.95,0:36:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.95,0:36:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your heavy footsteps gave you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.95,0:36:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Come in. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.96,0:36:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother's eyesight is not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.46,0:36:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.96,0:36:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This teacher is very tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.48,0:36:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.00,0:36:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.01,0:37:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Can't think when we last had a man home for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.51,0:37:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The food must taste good to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.02,0:37:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You sound like you're enjoying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.02,0:37:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.02,0:37:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}About a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.03,0:37:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Have you gotten used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.53,0:37:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.03,0:37:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.03,0:37:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You're from the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.03,0:37:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes, from East Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.03,0:37:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How did you choose Sanhetun?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.04,0:37:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}After graduation, I couldn't find work.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.04,0:37:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}One day in the street, a man was signing people up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.04,0:37:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I didn't know what for, but I signed up anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.54,0:38:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}And I ended up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.05,0:38:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Do you regret it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.05,0:38:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.55,0:38:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.55,0:38:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I like it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.55,0:38:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Are you married?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.56,0:38:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.06,0:38:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Are you engaged?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.56,0:38:16.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.07,0:38:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di will do it. Sit for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.59,0:38:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Do you remember this bowl?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.59,0:38:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This design?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.09,0:38:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No, I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.09,0:38:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Did you eat the food brought to the site?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.10,0:38:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.60,0:38:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Looks like Di's hard work was wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.60,0:39:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You know when you were building the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.61,0:39:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}she made all her best dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.61,0:39:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She always used that bowl,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.11,0:39:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}hoping you would choose her dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.61,0:39:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Even I wasn't allowed to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.12,0:39:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.62,0:39:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You do?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.62,0:39:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The bowl and your cooking are familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.12,0:39:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}So you ate from it before?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.63,0:39:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.63,0:39:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You did? What did you eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.63,0:39:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.13,0:39:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}On the first day, I made onion cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.64,0:39:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}On the second, scrambled eggs and onions on rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.14,0:39:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}On the third day, mushroom dumplings.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.64,0:39:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What a shame. Three delicious meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.65,0:39:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}And I love mushroom dumplings.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.15,0:39:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'll make you some this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.35,0:39:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That is too much to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.20,0:39:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.30,0:39:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You've hardly finished lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.30,0:39:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and you're planning the next meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.66,0:39:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di, show the teacher out. He must be very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.16,0:39:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes, I should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.68,0:40:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That red jacket of yours is pretty on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.18,0:40:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I remember it from the day I arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.18,0:40:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- Don't forget to come back for dumplings.    - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.20,0:40:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You shouldn't make the dumplings.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.70,0:40:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.20,0:40:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You may regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.20,0:40:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.20,0:40:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.21,0:40:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This teacher is a nice man,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.21,0:40:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but he's out of our class.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.21,0:40:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What are you talking about? It's only dumplings.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.71,0:40:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Don't play dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.22,0:40:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'm just being honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.72,0:40:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You'd best forget about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.74,0:41:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I will not go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.75,0:41:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You've got no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.85,0:43:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I came to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.35,0:43:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.86,0:43:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Back to the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.86,0:43:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.36,0:43:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.36,0:43:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I saw you argue with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.86,0:43:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Was that what it was about?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.87,0:43:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Who was he? Why do you have to go back?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.37,0:43:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.37,0:43:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They just want to ask me some questions. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.37,0:43:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Can't they ask you questions here?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.37,0:43:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He says it's not up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.38,0:43:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Will you come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.38,0:43:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Of course. I have classes to teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.88,0:43:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When will you be back?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.72,0:43:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}By the 27th at the latest.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.64,0:43:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}On the 28th, the school holiday starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.36,0:43:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I have to be back before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.40,0:43:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Come in and eat something.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.40,0:43:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.90,0:43:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I have things to do before I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.91,0:44:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I really do. That man is waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.41,0:44:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Tell him to come too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.41,0:44:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You have to eat in any case.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.42,0:44:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Okay, I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.92,0:44:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.92,0:44:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.93,0:44:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}To go with your red jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.94,0:44:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.44,0:44:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.00,0:44:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}What is going on? No more class?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.50,0:44:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He's in some political trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.95,0:44:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Political trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.46,0:44:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't understand it either. But maybe it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.06,0:44:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Said he might be back in a day or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.49,0:45:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The teacher's left.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.50,0:45:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The teacher's left?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.50,0:45:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.50,0:45:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Just left?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.50,0:45:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Just left with the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.27,0:50:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother retraced her steps every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.28,0:50:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}searching back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.28,0:50:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She had to find the clip my father had given her.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.72,0:52:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Pottery repairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.23,0:52:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Pottery repairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.23,0:52:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.82,0:53:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I charge for the nails I use.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.83,0:53:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This will cost you more than buying a new bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.33,0:53:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Just tell me how much, and I'll pay you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.33,0:53:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Is it a family heirloom?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.33,0:53:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.34,0:54:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It belonged to someone special?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.84,0:54:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.34,0:54:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.34,0:54:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's for my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.85,0:54:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The man who used it left
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.85,0:54:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and took my daughter's heart with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.86,0:54:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I've put it back together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.86,0:54:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I hope she'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.37,0:54:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Pottery repairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.40,0:55:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.90,0:55:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Nothing. Just getting a drink of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.45,0:55:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}1 times 8 equals 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.96,0:56:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}1 times 9 equals 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.46,0:56:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 2 equals 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.96,0:56:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 3 equals 6.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.97,0:56:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 4 equals 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.47,0:56:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 5 equals 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.47,0:56:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 6 equals 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.47,0:56:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 7 equals 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.48,0:56:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 8 equals 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.48,0:56:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}2 times 9 equals 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.98,0:56:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.96,0:56:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 3 equals 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.99,0:56:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 4 equals 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.49,0:56:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 5 equals 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.49,0:56:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 6 equals 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.00,0:56:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 7 equals 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.00,0:56:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 8 equals 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.00,0:56:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}3 times 9 equals 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.56,0:57:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My father told my mother
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.56,0:57:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}when he was teaching the kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.56,0:57:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}he could always look up and see the red banner.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.07,0:57:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When he saw that banner
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.07,0:57:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}it reminded him of Mother and her red jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.57,0:57:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor kept insisting
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.57,0:57:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}that the ceiling needed proper insulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.58,0:58:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but my father never let him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.08,0:58:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's why the school ceiling was never completed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.12,1:00:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother sat in the classroom for hours that day.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.62,1:00:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The door was open, and the mayor saw her there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.13,1:00:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He understood what that meant.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.63,1:00:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Once he knew,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.63,1:00:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}the news got around the village, quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.13,1:00:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Back then, arranged matches were the rule.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.14,1:00:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The freedom of falling in love was unfamiliar.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.14,1:00:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This was a first for our village.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.40,1:00:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}On the day my father promised to return...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.90,1:00:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my mother was waiting from first light.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.41,1:00:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She remembered his promise:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.91,1:00:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}that he would return on the 27th.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.41,1:00:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}School vacation began on the 28th.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.42,1:00:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He had to be back before that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.98,1:03:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's so cold out. Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.48,1:03:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Gone all day. Get warm on the bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.99,1:03:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You're burning up!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.53,1:04:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I know you went to wait for the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.03,1:04:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Everyone says he's in trouble and won't be back.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.64,1:04:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You've got to let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.54,1:04:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I'm going to the city to find him.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.54,1:04:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Are you crazy?! You're ill!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.05,1:04:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di! Come back!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.09,1:05:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother didn't make it to the city.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.09,1:05:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She fainted by the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.59,1:05:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Someone saw her, and they got word to the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.60,1:05:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor and my uncle brought her home on a cart.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.60,1:05:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor said that day,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.20,1:05:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my mother's hands were like ice.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.90,1:05:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}While on the cart,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.11,1:05:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}they wrapped her in a heavy blanket,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.11,1:05:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but they couldn't get her hands warm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.12,1:05:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't think it's too serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.12,1:05:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's a bad chill, but she is strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.63,1:05:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mayor, is the teacher coming back?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.14,1:05:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't know the answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.64,1:06:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He should have been back by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.64,1:06:07.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Maybe someone can write to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.65,1:06:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't know how to help her...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.15,1:06:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}if he doesn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.58,1:06:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Spring is here."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.03,1:06:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Spring is here."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.54,1:06:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"It melts the snow."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.52,1:06:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"It melts the snow."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.01,1:06:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The grass turns green."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.51,1:06:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The grass turns green."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.01,1:06:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The farmers sow."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.52,1:06:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The farmers sow."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.02,1:06:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The ox plow the field."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.52,1:06:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The ox plow the field."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.52,1:06:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The wild geese return."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.52,1:06:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The wild geese return."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.03,1:06:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The frogs begin to hop."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.53,1:06:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The frogs begin to hop."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.03,1:06:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di, you're awake.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.53,1:07:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You've been sleeping for two days.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.53,1:07:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di, the teacher is back.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.23,1:07:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The teacher is back.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.04,1:07:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He came back yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.04,1:07:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He came straight here.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.04,1:07:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He sat with you for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.55,1:07:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Isn't it good news?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.05,1:07:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He came back for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.05,1:07:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Full of energy."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.06,1:07:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Our spirit comes alive."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.56,1:07:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Our spirit comes alive."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.06,1:07:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"It carries our wishes."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.07,1:07:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"It carries our wishes."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.57,1:07:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Full of hope."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.07,1:07:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Full of hope."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.58,1:07:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Spring is here."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.09,1:07:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Spring is here."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.08,1:07:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"It melts the snow."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.58,1:07:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"It melts the snow."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.58,1:07:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The grass turns green."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.59,1:07:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The grass turns green."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.59,1:07:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The farmers sow."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.09,1:07:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The farmers sow."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.09,1:08:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The ox plow the field."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.09,1:08:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The ox plow the field."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.60,1:08:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The wild geese return."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.10,1:08:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The wild geese return."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.60,1:08:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The frogs begin to hop."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.10,1:08:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The frogs begin to hop."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.61,1:08:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Swallows start to sing."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.11,1:08:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Swallows start to sing."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.62,1:08:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Spring is the season to sow."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.13,1:08:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Spring is the season to sow."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.12,1:08:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"All starts to grow again."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.62,1:08:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"All starts to grow again."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.63,1:08:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The world is full of life again."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.14,1:08:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"The world is full of life again."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.63,1:08:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mr. Luo!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.63,1:08:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mr. Luo, Di is here to see you!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.64,1:08:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Sir!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.65,1:08:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Di is here!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.18,1:08:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That evening, my father had to leave again.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.15,1:08:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When he heard about my mother, he left the city...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.15,1:08:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}without permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.15,1:09:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He couldn't stand it any longer,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.15,1:09:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}so he sneaked back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.66,1:09:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}For this disobedience,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.16,1:09:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my parents were kept apart for another two years.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.67,1:09:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Someone told me,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.17,1:09:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}that on the day my father finally returned,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.17,1:09:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my mother put on her red jacket,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.67,1:09:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my father's favorite,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.18,1:09:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and stood by the road to wait for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.68,1:09:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}From that day on, my father never left my mother again.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.20,1:09:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This is the story of my father and my mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.20,1:09:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}This road is part of their love story...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.21,1:09:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}this road that leads from the city to our village.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.71,1:10:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Maybe because of the hope it held for her
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.72,1:10:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}as she waited for my father to return,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.72,1:10:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}she wants to walk this way with him one last time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.73,1:10:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mr. Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.23,1:10:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mr. Mayor?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.73,1:10:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.73,1:10:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's me, Yusheng.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.74,1:10:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- You need to see me?    - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.24,1:10:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Come in, come in. It's cold out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.74,1:10:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.25,1:10:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I've thought it through.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.75,1:10:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I want to do as my mother wishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.25,1:10:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}To carry him back?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.25,1:10:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's still a problem, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.76,1:10:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The problem is not enough men, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.76,1:10:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How about this:
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.26,1:10:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We'll hire men from the next village.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.76,1:10:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.27,1:10:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}But how do we pay them?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.27,1:10:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Just tell me how many men we need.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.27,1:11:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}For a short distance, only 10,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.28,1:11:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but this is a long trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.28,1:11:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I think we need about 16.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.78,1:11:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We will need two shifts. That's 32 men.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.79,1:11:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}And we'll need others to carry chairs,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.10,1:11:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}so people can rest along the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.29,1:11:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That comes to about 35, 36 men.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.30,1:11:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How much per person?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.80,1:11:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}One hundred yuan each should do.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.30,1:11:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That will do.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.81,1:11:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Thirty-five, 36 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.31,1:11:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How much in total?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.31,1:11:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That's 3500 or 3600 yuan.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.81,1:11:44.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We need to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.82,1:11:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}And wine too, gotta ward off the cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.82,1:11:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We'll also want a little extra for emergency use.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.83,1:11:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Altogether, around 4000 yuan.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.34,1:12:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Here's 5000 yuan. Is that enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.34,1:12:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}It's more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.39,1:13:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mrs. Luo, come and see Mr. Luo.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.90,1:13:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Please don't cry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.90,1:13:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Don't let tears fall on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.91,1:13:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mr. Luo, we are going back to the village.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.92,1:13:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}That day over 100 people came to the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.92,1:13:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor told me they were my father's students.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.42,1:13:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They heard about his death, and they all came back.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.43,1:13:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Many came from other towns.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.93,1:13:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Some drove from the city.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.93,1:13:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor said some came from as far as Guangzhou.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.44,1:13:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Some tried, but didn't make it in time,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.44,1:13:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}because of the snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.94,1:13:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I didn't recognize many of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.45,1:13:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Many were older than me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.95,1:13:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I don't know when my father taught them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.95,1:14:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I didn't know how to address them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.96,1:14:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Anyway, as the mayor said,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.46,1:14:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}they are all my father's students.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.96,1:14:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Take this money back.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.46,1:14:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why? Didn't you pay the men?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.97,1:14:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They won't take it, not even the ones we hired.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.47,1:14:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No one wants the money.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.47,1:14:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Take it back.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.13,1:17:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}At my mother's request,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.64,1:17:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my father was buried next to the old well.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.14,1:17:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The village has running water now, so no one needs a well.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.64,1:17:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No one draws water from it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.15,1:17:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother says from this hill,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.15,1:17:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}my father can look down on the school.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.15,1:17:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}She asks to be buried next to him when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.70,1:17:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}After my father's funeral,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.67,1:17:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}the mayor came to talk about rebuilding the school.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.17,1:17:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The city has granted funds,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.78,1:17:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and the village families have donated money.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.68,1:17:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He says we must fulfill my father's wishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.48,1:17:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your money, give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.69,1:18:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mayor, we've saved over the years.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.20,1:18:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Take it to rebuild the school.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.70,1:18:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I can't take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.00,1:18:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}With my husband gone, you have to take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.21,1:18:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}All right, I'll take it then.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.22,1:18:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You are the first, but surely not the last, to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.71,1:18:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I am leaving tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.22,1:18:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother has asked me to go to the schoolhouse one last time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.22,1:18:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}My mother says the next time I come back,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.22,1:18:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}the school we know will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.73,1:18:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your father helped build this school.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.23,1:18:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He taught here so many years.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.24,1:18:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Spent as much time here as at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.24,1:18:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Changyu, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.25,1:18:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor will rebuild the school.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.25,1:19:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They'll build a tall
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.76,1:19:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and wonderful school...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.26,1:19:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}just as you wished.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.27,1:19:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}They will start building next spring.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.27,1:19:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You won't have to worry anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.78,1:19:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}When the school is completed,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.78,1:19:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I will hang a lucky red banner there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.29,1:19:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You can rest easy now.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.30,1:19:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You know, your father was a sincere man.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.76,1:19:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He always wanted you to become a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.76,1:20:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}to take over for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.76,1:20:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You went to the teachers' college,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.77,1:20:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}but you never taught a day of class.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.77,1:20:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}If you could teach for one day,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.78,1:20:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I think it would make him happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.28,1:20:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Then you can go back to your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.29,1:20:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Look, there's no teacher now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.30,1:20:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No sound of children reciting their lessons.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.30,1:20:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}The mayor said a new teacher was on the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.31,1:20:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Not many teachers,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.31,1:20:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}would sound as good as your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.32,1:20:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}After 40 years, I still love that voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.32,1:21:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I can still hear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.83,1:21:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother, I've been thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.33,1:21:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Why don't you come to the city with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.34,1:21:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.84,1:21:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I won't leave your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.34,1:21:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}How can I leave you here alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.35,1:21:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.35,1:21:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I can take care of myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.85,1:21:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Are you doing all right in the city?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.36,1:21:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.36,1:21:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.86,1:21:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Do you have a girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.86,1:21:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Let's not talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.87,1:21:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You're not young anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.37,1:21:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Don't be so picky.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.37,1:21:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.37,1:21:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Find yourself a nice girl
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.38,1:21:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}and bring her home to meet me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.39,1:22:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your father's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.89,1:22:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}He used to worry about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.90,1:22:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Our children must leave home.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.40,1:22:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}We can't keep you here forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.91,1:22:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}As parents...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.92,1:22:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}we let you go, but we never stopped worrying.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.92,1:22:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Your father...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.43,1:22:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}...missed you so.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.94,1:22:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}- Please don't cry.    - Your father...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.07,1:22:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}Mother, please don't cry.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.44,1:23:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}With your father gone, it's hard not to feel lonely.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.95,1:23:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.45,1:23:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}You...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.96,1:23:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}...must work hard and make a good life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.50,1:24:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"One must learn to read and write."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.00,1:24:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"One must learn to read and write."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.01,1:24:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Keep a journal faithfully."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.01,1:24:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Keep a journal faithfully."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.52,1:24:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Know the present, know the past."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.02,1:24:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\rEng}"Know the present, know the past."
